title: The production of positron emitters 75Br and 76Br- excitation functions and yields for 3He and alpha- particle induced nuclear reactions on arsenic.

x4freetext: The production of positron emitters 75Br and 76Br-
excitation functions and yields for 3He and alpha-
particle induced nuclear reactions on arsenic.
BIB section upgraded.
Correction in sub.004,009 -Rel-Ref,
according M.Bossant comment -SB
.Compact cyclotron `CV28`
.The checks were also made
using Cu and Al monitor foils inserted in different
places of the stack.The list of monitoring reactions
and the references for this monitors see in original
paper.
Each target consisted of metallic arsenic suspended
in a self-supporting polystyrene film. The films were
prepared by pouring a suspension of as powder in a
benzene solution of polystyrene on a thin `Al` sheet.
this method is very convenient since a number of
uniformly thin target samples can Be easily prepared.
on the other hand, these targets have the
disadvantages of low heat conductance and low melting
point, thereby limiting their use at low beam
currents of the incident particles. A stack consisted
at maximum of 12 targets. The amount of arsenic in
each individual target was determined after the
completion of the experiment by neutron activation
analysis to Be between 2.5 And 80 mg/cm**2, that of
polystyrene by weighing the target and substracting
the amount of arsenic.

x4freetext: . DECAY DATA.
/BY AUTHORS/.
SINCE MOST OF THE GAMMA-LINES OF 76BR ARE THE SAME
AS THOSE IN  THE DECAY OF 76AS, BOTH DECAYING TO
76SE, AND 76AS IS FORMED SIMULTANEOUSLY BY THE
(3HE,2P) AND (ALPHA,2PN) REACTIONS, RESPECTIVELY, WE
HAD TO USE FOR 76BR THE RELATIVELY WEAK LINE OF 1853
KEV (14.0 PER CENT) WITH LOWER DETECTION EFFICIENCY
INSTEAD OF THE STRONGER ONES 559 KEV (72.4 PER CENT)
AND  657 KEV (15.5 PER CENT). THE 1853 KEV
GAMMA-LINE, HOWEVER, IS NOT EMITTED IN THE DECAY OF
76AS. MEASUREMENT OF THE DECAY OF 1853 KEV SHOWS A
HALF-LIFE OF 15.7 HRS., A VALUE COMPARABLE TO THE
ACCEPTED ONE OF 16.0 HRS. THE 559 KEV LINE SHOWS A
LONGER HALF-LIFE (E.G.,17.2 HRS.). 76AS, HOWEVER, DOES
NOT EMIT ANY STRONG GAMMA-LINE WHICH IS NOT GIVEN
OUT IN THE DECAY OF 76BR. USING THE 559 KEV
GAMMA-LINE THE TOTAL ACTIVITY DUE TO 76BR+76AS WAS
DETERMINED AND THE CONTRIBUTION OF 76AS WAS OBTAINED
BY SUBTRACTION(34).

/BY AUTHORS/. SIMULTANEOUS FORMATION OF 38.8-H 77AS
BY THE (ALPHA,2P) AND OF 56-H 77BR BY THE (ALPHA,2N)
REACTION NO CONTRIBUTION OF 77AS TO 97.5 PER CENT
INTO THE GROUND STATE OF 77SE AND SO THE GAMMA-YIELD

IT IS TO BE EXPECTED THAT THE (ALPHA,2P) REACTION
SHOULD HAVE A HUNDRED-FOLD LOWER YIELD THAT THE
(ALPHA,2N) REACTION.
